	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Q: Ok, I have this pulling thing going well now. We are into the swing of things and the group likes that I am chain pulling. My only problem is that I have TONS of spare mana!<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Pull with a poison dot, and slow afterwards is an option.  You'll have massive aggro, but do much better damage than nuking.<br />
<br />
Another option is to mem a nuke and nuke when you can.  Ya, our nukes suck compared to other classes, but if you have too much mana, you gotta spend it on something.<br />
<br />
Another option is to do heals, and let the main healer do nukes.  Clerics have a 4:1 dmg:mana ratio undead nuke with a -100 resist mod.  Druids have a 3.97:1 dmg:mana ratio cold nuke and 3.94:1 ratio fire nuke.  Shaman can play main healer and slower with druid/cleric doing backup heals.  It's not conventional, but it's probably more efficient in terms of damage dealing.</p>
	
	
	
