<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Piglet</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Nov 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I've used AV a few times, but it does soak up a bit of time waiting for a refresh so that you can chain it onto the next mob. Handy for rooms with narrow entrances that you just can't see enough of with an F9 but overall: stalking probe > both.<br />
<br />
Nice point on the VP btw, 'bouncing' a mob out of the way to split works quite well and if you do it right you can actually paralyse a centre mob, bounce him closer to another and agro that one into camp (proximity agro so train him onto the fighting tank to buy you the space to slow-agro and root-park), then go back and pick off the third mob which is now stood on it's own and either bring that in too or root it and start rotting the both of them ready for the group to move up when they're done with what they have.<br />
<br />
Pet pulling works a treat at splitting busy rooms and also buying time on adds for slows etc to land (SKs love that tactic for pulling with their otherwise horrid little pets).<br />
<br />
Nuking is a good option to soak up the spare mana. It's also handy for breaking root on parked mobs that you want in camp now, so having it up already saves time re-memming.<br />
<br />
Lots of good info in there Caanus. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><br />
<br />
Edit: Oh yeah, just remembered another little trick to avoid getting beaten on if you get a multi pull. If you've left dogdog guarding by the group or better yet attacking the engaged mob, and you're pulling mobs in from a few rooms away (depends on dungeon type, some like Ruj don't have doors, others like Mir have loads of rooms), as you pull hit /pet back off and then /pet follow. By the time you get through the first door, dogdog should be well on his way to you and all the doors on the route to the group will be open. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /> If you think you're gonna have problems once you get back to the group, that's also the time that you can suicide the puppy onto the mobs to get some of them under control early (as per the "Well, I was unlucky and got 3+ mobs... Are we lost?" section).</p>
	
	
	
	
		<div class="smallfont"><i>Last edited by Piglet on 09-22-2003 at <span class="time">01:46 PM</span>. </i></div>
	
	
