	<!-- message -->
	<p>Very good post on pulling with a shaman, better then anything I could find on Monkly-Business at the time<br />
<br />
My main is a monk and I pull evertime I group with him and will attest that all that pathing info is correct.<br />
<br />
Been having some bad pullers in my group with my shaman so I might suggest pulling with him from now on.  <br />
<br />
The only problem I can see with Root pulling to hold off an add is the very rare occurance of wanderers (they are there...just not very often).<br />
<br />
If you cast root while the mob is at its innitial bind spot then a wonderer could come by and agro the rest of the room, and the wanderer on you...Scouting should fix this problem though.<br />
<br />
Thank you very much for the info.<br />
