</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Actually monks can pull fairly well even in LDoN.  They just have to get used to the fact that they can't pull only singles.  a monk with good skill in pulling should have no problem pulling 2 at a time and offtanking one till it gets mezzed, slowed, or root parked behind the group.<br />
<br />
Pulling is a mentality, add in tools to that and you have the end product.   Monks have the ability to abort if an initial pull goes bad.  Shaman have the ability to park adds (very effective just got done trying it) and that Pac/Harmony classes have the ability to pick and choose who to pull (But generally takes about as much time as me pulling fom what I have seen and takes mana).<br />
<br />
The most effective way a monk can FD pull in LDoN is to manipulate the pathing, get very close to the direct melee area of one mob and that one mob will follow you in a straight line...however the other ones will not they will path...get the one you have directly pathing to the group and FD.  The others will usually be right outside of agro range if you do it right...takes skill but once you figure it out its easy.  This is very effective in Mistmoore.<br />
***EDIT***<br />
Jeebus I spell good (note to self: Proofread before posting)<br />
***EDIT***<br />
____________________<br />
Brother Meladrak Doushi<br />
