<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Juujuu</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Heyokah<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 1999<br />
	Location: Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Don't use Assiduous Vision if you have Vision.  Why?<br />
Look at what the 2 of them do:<br />
<a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=580&amp;source=Live" target="_blank">Vision</a> <br />
<a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=384&amp;source=Live" target="_blank">Assiduous Vision</a> <br />
<br />
Both spells do this:<br />
Slot Description <br />
1:  Bind Sight <br />
2:  Increase Magnification by 130% <br />
3:  Ultravision <br />
<br />
The differences between them:<br />
Vision costs 10 mana instead of 50.<br />
Vision has a 4 casting time instead of 6.<br />
Vision has a 10 casting time instead of 12.<br />
AVision has a 15 fizzle adjustment instead of 25 for Vision, whatever that's worth.<br />
<br />
AV lasts 1.95 hours at Level 39<br />
AV lasts 3.25 hours at Level 65<br />
Vision lasts 4.8 mins at Level 19<br />
Vision lasts 14.0 mins at Level 65<br />
<br />
Vision takes less time to cast, recast, and needs less mana.<br />
The only downside is its duration is crap compared to AV.<br />
But when you are pulling in a dungeon and a mob is dying every 60 seconds, who needs a 3 hour duration (even more with scrm + focus effects <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" />?</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><img src="http://members.shaw.ca/mpatterson64/juujuusigsmall.jpg" border="0" alt=""> <br />
