</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I have to agree with anyone using the pet pull technique... this is by far one of our best pulling techniques in higher level dungeons (such as LDON hard missions).  Since LDON came out I have pet as one of my perma memmed spells for the sole purpose of pulling.<br />
<br />
One problem with using Spirit Call to pull though is that it requires line of sight... if you have line of sight, use it, if you don't... well yer pup's rdy to die for you if he can't back off fast enough.<br />
<br />
Also one of my favorite items to use to break root parked mobs (that were rooted during a root split) is White Ceramic Band... it is usable from inventory and casts a 3 second Burst of Flame.  Beats the heck outa keeping a nuke loaded, waiting for root to break, or having to use a short duration root.<br />
<br />
Lately I've been using pet to pull so much it's almost making Suspended Minion sound good.<br />
<br />
Lets see... something that wasn't listed... a good spell line up for pullers (sorry I'm assuming lvl 65 on this).<br />
<br />
Tnarg's<br />
Q<br />
Can4<br />
Pet<br />
Malos<br />
Tugurs<br />
Paralyzing Earth<br />
Vision (if you don't like knowing your pull go with FA or Buff Swap slot... Malos normally best slot to swap for buffing during this situation though)</p>
	
	
	
