<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Ronax</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Teacher<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jun 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />It flies in the direction you are facing and WILL AGGRO OTHERS BASED ON WHERE IT LANDS, not based on where it was when VP hit it.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>I feel like I have to add some information about VP.  In my experience a mob will aggro from where it was when you cast it, not from where it lands.  I have spent a lot of time in Droga, and with the tiny aggro range there, it should be trivial to split mobs if it worked the way described in the original post.<br />
<br />
Also, throughout this post I have seen many people misuse the term pet-pulling.  Pet pulling is not sending in your level 61 pet and dealing with the adds as they come chasing you out.  Pet pulling is sending in a lower level pet (spirit of the howler) into a room full of tightly packed mobs and only one comes out.  Your pet must survive initial aggro, or this will not work.  Once the pet dies aggro will work like it always does.<br />
<br />
I have used pet pulling successfully in Droga at any camp, for guarenteed singles.  I have also used it for pulling Drusella Sathirs room solo in HS.  This method will probably not work in high risk ldon, Gates of Discord, or in the elementals due to how hard mobs hit.</p>
	
	
	
